    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for high-upside output today, anchored by the elite tier of **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.77). **Kyle Tucker** draws a prime matchup against Feltner in a hitter-friendly environment, and his score is bolstered by a significant 14% park boost and favorable SP skill metrics. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** thrives in the leadoff spot; his projection remains robust despite the minor penalty for facing an elite hold-percentage arm, as his volume and dynamic platoon advantage provide a high floor for the 5x5 categories. Also keep an eye on **Andy Pages**, who leverages that same favorable park factor against Feltner to reach a strong 74.43 score, with an added boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which optimizes his potential for stolen base accumulation.\n\nRegarding our bench decisions, **Nasim Nunez** was the most difficult exclusion, finishing at a 57.95 efficiency. While **Nasim Nunez** offers elite speed, his lower batting order position and the defensive efficiency of the opposing catcher ultimately capped his total points, pushing him behind the established reliability of starters like **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill**. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Drake Baldwin** (48.10), as his matchup against S\u00e1nchez presents a challenge; his sub-50 score suggests he is on the fringe of our bench threshold, but he remains in the lineup due to our current lack of viable alternatives. Monitor the weather in all venues, but for today, the primary risk remains the high-skill matchup for **Drake Baldwin** and the platoon regression affecting **Jackson Merrill** against the southpaw Kikuchi.",
